Blocks.Text: Here's a step-by-step tutorial on how to integrate EdenAI's invoice parsing API
1- Create a Retool project and go to the Resources tab.
2- Click Create new and select REST API to create a new resource. This
will open a resource page where you can add your connection information.
3- Enter a name for the resource (e.g. "EdenAI API") then paste in the API
endpoint https://api.edenai.run along with the header and your bearer API key
obtained after creating your EdenAI account.
4- Now your Retool UI, add a file input component for the invoice file.
5- To create an API request to edenai, you need to use the invoice parser end-
point (v2/ocr/invoice_parser) and change the request body format to form
Then, add the required payload data which includes the providers you want to
call, the language of your file, and the invoice file itself.
Since the API request is a multipart request, you must also send both the file
metadata and data using the javascript spread operator
6- Test the API request to make sure it is working as expected.
If you encounter a timeout error, increase the limit in the advanced tab of your
7- You can add a button component to trigger the API request.

Note: This tutorial assumes that you already created an EdenAI account and
have access to your API key.
